ass=title> accessability options for disabled players</span><hr size=1> pass this around and discuss it<br>
<br>
I’ve been playing EverQuest for a few years now, and I’ve ran into an unique issue. For the last 27 years I’ve had a neuromuscular disease, which is physical disability that deteriorates my muscles; making it more difficult or impossible to do tasks which seem easy to the able-bodied world. So, the issue I’m being faced with is typing with a keyboard, in fact i'm using an on screen keyboard to write this letter. If your unfamiliar with on-screen keyboards, it basically allows me to use the mouse to select letters, which then are displayed on screen as if you’re typing using standard keyboard.  Typing has become an issue with-in the world of EverQuest, making my playing time become near nothing. Which troubles me severely because its something I enjoy immensely, it has become something that I spend many of hours researching, reading and learning about. Since typing is a very integral part of EverQuest not being able to type is a hindrance. <br>
<br>
Now, the main reason I have decided to write is; has this issue been brought up to the developers behind EverQuest?  If not what I’m hoping for is an option, which might assist me in typing; such as an on-screen keyboard. With the ever evolving world and/or interface EverQuest has gone through it would seem as if this feature would be a viable feature of EverQuest that would be a benefit.  It maybe an issue people other then myself have or could have in the future, and having options would allow for a missing sector of the population to be involved in the mass appeal of a game such as EverQuest. <br>
